reviews.title: Great food. Friendly staff.
reviews.text:
Fine world restaurant.Well a bit small.But well we are spoiled I know.Enough choice of food.Friendly staff.Mix of kind of people what comes here.But well we do not come for that.We will probably come back here sometime.
Highly recommended😎

reviews.title: Dust
reviews.text: Was really cozy...good food is nothing with that...we had a table with poetry lamps above..all the dust that was on it just swirled after downstairs in my food and drink..really a shame...only thing they were going to do that the next x is clean..

reviews.title: Top for children, moderate for adults.
reviews.text:
Top for the kids: choose everything yourself, unlimited drinks / desserts, and even cotton candy. 

But the three adults at the table found the food very mediocre. The sushi was ok, as well as the cold starters. But the Chinese food in baking was not good, the wok was disappointing, the pizza was visibly not a nice fresh Italian pizza, the pancakes were dry. 

I thought it was not very worldly/wide anyway. It's more like a Chinese wok restaurant, with a few other choices.

reviews.title: Everything was perfect
reviews.text: Very cozy place and the staff is always friendly!! The food was delicious and there is a lot of choice. We will definitely be back. What I also noticed is that the glasses and plates were very clean, also important.

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text: At restaurant Breed I really enjoyed it! Great food, top service and a cozy atmosphere. Highly recommended! We will definitely be back.

reviews.title: too much food!
reviews.text:
Very nice and clean set up. Many different dishes, too many really. 
Overall quality was better then an average USA all you can eat.

reviews.title: Good place for all you can eat concept
reviews.text:
Breed is one of the few good all you can eat restaurants in Groningen. The times I have gone the food has always been excellent. The same goes for the sushi, which mostly isn't that great at an all you can eat restaurant.
The service is excellent and fast (clearing up empty plates and glasses). And the workers are always friendly to you. 

There is a huge variety of different foods for practically any person.

Small improvements (during my time): 

-  Is that the fish on the grill was slightly on the saltish side on some parts of the fish, but this can be due to different preferences or that the soy sauce was not spread properly over the fish. 
- The next one is that the scallops were really really small.
- Lastly the bbq steak, is never cooked medium when asked. We always got ours well done instead of medium. 

Overall, the food and staff were great.

reviews.title: Very clean modern Buffett
reviews.text: Very nice great food selection. Ate a ton of shrimp. So much sushi. Great selection of desserts and drinks.  In the basement is a large play area for kids. A nice young woman did facepainting for the kids too. Only thing is that it cost a bit  we paid almost 80€ for the family. 2 adults 2 kids under 7. Without alcoholic beverages.  The quality was great but a little over out budget

reviews.title: Good all you can eat restaurant with broad choice
reviews.text: Nice restaurant where you pay for the time you stay and eat as much as you can. There is a very wide choice of dishes with grill, wok, sushi, fried etc. etc. Good quality. Standard drinks are included and special drinks are not expensive. Also very good to bring children along as it has a very large playroom for kids.

reviews.title: Extremely good quality, not for romantic dining
reviews.text: I was having doubts about this restaurant which caters for large groups. However, the quality of the food was excellent and well prepared. The concept is that you pay for a certain time you want to eat (2 or 3 hours) and you eat and drink all you want. Only alcohol is extra. There is Japanese, Indian, Indonesian food, fresh vegetables, fish and meat prepared while you wait to your liking. Very large choice. There also is an extensive desert buffet. Nice if you are celebrating a birthday, but not for a romantic tete-a-tete. There is a special room for children.

reviews.title: Much better then expected
reviews.text:
As it is a restaurant with several cuisines my expectations were not high. But I this restaurant was a nice surprise, the food  was good if not excellent. The atmosphere modern, not crowded. You pay for the time You want to stay, the food is free during this time. You only pay extra for alcohol beverages . 
I like the concept and the way it is implemented, I will come back.

reviews.title: Perfect for families
reviews.text:
A buffet restaurant with a cellar for kids to play, get their faces painted or watch a cartoon.
The buffet is extensive and replenished regularly and on time.  There is also a corner for pancakes and stir fry.  Two chocolate fountains are of course a children's destination.
Time in the restaurant is unfortunately limited to two hours only.  For the rest, all good.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ guide for families
tripContent.description: "As a two-mom family who has been traveling to Orlando five to six times a year, we see the city like a second home. We absolutely love the theme parks but Orlando has so much more to offer! We love experiencing Orlando's rich diversity, fantastic food, incredible art and culture, plus a fun soccer game here and there. Join me, Allison Mertzman, as I share some of my family's favorite Orlando attractions with you!" - Allison Mertzman
